{{see|Jones}}
==English==

===Etymology===
Ed Boland, in the ''New York Times'', March 2002, attributes the term to heroin addicts who frequented Great Jones Alley in New York City between Broadway and Lafayette, although the slang term has been around much longer.

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg-es}}

# An addiction or intense craving.
#: ''I've got a basketball '''jones'''!''

===Intransitive verb===
{{en-infl-reg-sibilant|jon|es|}}

# To have an intense craving.
#:''I'm '''jonesing''' for some basketball.''
# {{rare}} To steal or to take, usually without permission.
#:''Hey, I'm going to '''jones''' some cookies from Cory.''

